### Obsidian-Style Interactive Knowledge Graph
We will implement an interactive HTML5 Canvas 2D Force-Directed Graph view directly inside the frontend, which will be 100% offline-ready.

#### Graph Physics Model
The physics model operates in real-time on visual nodes using the following forces:
- **Gravity Force**: Pulls all nodes toward the center of the canvas:
  $$F_{gravity} = -c_g \cdot (\vec{p}_{node} - \vec{p}_{center})$$
- **Repulsive Force (Charge)**: Nodes push away from each other to prevent overlapping (similar to Coulomb's Law):
  $$F_{repulsion} = \frac{c_r}{d^2}$$
- **Attractive Force (Spring)**: Connected nodes are pulled together along relationship edges (similar to Hooke's Law):
  $$F_{attraction} = c_s \cdot (d - d_{rest})$$
- **Drag Damping**: Dampens velocities over time to stabilize the layout naturally.

#### Relations (Edges) Model
- **Explicit Links**: Generated by parsing the body or title of node A for `#XXXX` references or the `[[#XXXX]]` pattern. An arrowhead represents the direction.
- **Tag Links**: Soft, toggleable dashed connections drawn between any two nodes sharing at least one tag.

